The paper discusses the use of natural language in human-robot cooperation, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) category. The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in NLC-based robotic systems. The analysis of natural language processing (NLP) techniques used in NLC-based systems falls under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) category. The paper also discusses the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect of NLC-based systems. Lastly, the paper discusses future research trends, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) category.
